  "text": "The cytoplasmic domain of mGITR and hGITR is respectively 52 and 53 amino acid residues long, and shows a good homology with the cytoplasmic domains of OX40, 4-1BB and CD27 (similarity between 45 and 50%)( Figure 5 ) [CITATION_1] . The homologies span the complete cytoplasmic domain but are centered in 2 segments: domain 1, the sequence next to the -COOH terminus of transmembrane region, and domain 2, close to the -COOH terminus of the proteins ( Figure 5 ). Interestingly, domains 1 and 2 are coded by different exons [CITATION_2] .",
